For {= company =}+ companies, supply public source evidence about companies operating in, manufacturing for, distributing into, renting or servicing, or supplying the North American drill-tool, drill-collar, downhole-tool, oilfield tubular, or A519/mechanical-tubing ecosystem; cover each of the {= capability_facet =} capability facets below for every company with a company-specific source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per facet).

The useful public facts are the source-stated role, North America signal when visible, source class, visible source date, checked date, and the source-stated capability claim. Current public evidence is best; dated catalogs, line sheets, standards pages, registry pages, and articles are fine when they still visibly carry the company-specific claim.

Capability facets:
- `product_role`: source-stated product, supply, manufacturing, distribution, rental, service, tubing, drill-collar, downhole-tool, or oilfield-tubular role.
- `material_or_standard`: source-stated material, grade, specification, standard, certification, or quality claim tied to the company's capability.
- `dimension_or_capability_range`: source-stated size, OD, ID, wall, connection, inventory, facility, process, or other capability range.

Out of scope: supplier ranking, procurement recommendations, quote solicitation, contacts, lead scoring, pricing outreach, compatibility advice, safety or engineering adequacy conclusions, and inferred A519-to-drill-collar suitability.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the named company.
- The page should be a public company-specific capability source for the selected facet. Company-owned product pages, capability pages, catalogs, specification sheets, line sheets, facility pages, distributor line cards, certification or registry pages, and trade articles can work when the company and facet claim are visible; search results, marketplaces, generic directories, rankings, contact pages alone, and pages that only mention a brand in passing do not.
- The page must state a capability claim for the selected facet. `product_role` needs a stated product or operating role; `material_or_standard` needs a stated material, grade, standard, specification, certification, or quality claim; `dimension_or_capability_range` needs a stated size, range, connection, inventory, facility, process, or comparable capability limit.
